page.title: 06St.Clement walk
page.content: The St. Clement walk along-side the River Fal is very interesting.The river is very muddy and slippery.That is a disadvantage to boat owners because when the tide is out it is very shallow and the boats that are moored there get stuck in the mud. There are lots of different birds that live by the river such as black headed gulls, kingfishers, cormorants, wood pigeons, curlews and mallards. It is good for fishing in the river. You can catch fish such as flounder, mullet,bass and the occasional sea trout. In the wood land are trees such as beech,oak,ash,horsechestnut, sycamore, blackthorn and hawthorn.If you walk down the path by the river,on your right is the land owned by the Duchy of Cornwall.On the opposite bank is part of Lord Falmouth's estate.
